react_usage.answer:
Yes! Each store can use a different URL parameter: ```tsx
const useCartStore = create(/* ... */, { key: 'cart' })
const useFiltersStore = create(/* ... */, { key: 'filters' })
```
This creates URLs like `?cart=...&filters=...`

use_cases.answer:
Store todos, filters, and views: ```tsx
const useTodoStore = create((set) => ({
  todos: [],
  filter: 'all', // 'all', 'active', 'completed'
  view: 'list',
  addTodo: (text) => set(state => ({ 
    todos: [...state.todos, { id: Date.now(), text, done: false }] 
  }))
}), { compress: true })
```
Users can share filtered views or specific todo lists.

frameworks.answer:
Absolutely! The core package is framework-agnostic: ```js
import { encodeState, decodeState } from '@farajabien/slug-store-core'

// Manual URL management
const state = { items: [] }
const slug = await encodeState(state)
window.history.replaceState({}, '', `?state=${slug}`)
```
